{"title":"Esker Cycles Hits the Refresh Button on its Hardtail Lineup","link":"https://bikerumor.com/esker-cycles-hardtail-lineup-updated-hayduke-lvs-japhy-lorax-ti/","date":1741628144000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-Ti-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" alt=\"(Photos / Esker Cycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Updated Hayduke Lives! <a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Esker Cycles</a> has refreshed and updated most of its hardtail lineup. The two staple hardtails, Hayduke and Japhy, see key geometry updates and some new frame features, while the Lorax Ti and Hayduke LVS only see “minor tweaks”, but that includes the Hitching Post accessory mount. This leaves the Lorax, Smokey, and Smokey Ti untouched.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Update first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Update-first-pic-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / Esker Cycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s see what’s new! </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Hitching Post</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"951\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates hitching post\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post-297x221.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post-120x89.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hitching-post-768x571.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Hitching Post</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All updated titanium frames will see the addition of The Hitching Post. This added feature is a modification to the seat tube, moving the bottle mounts further forward. This allows for more seat post insertion–since the post won’t bottom out on the bolts–and adds a place to strap down some additional gear if not using it as a standard bottle cage mount. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Hayduke Updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates full hayduke\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-full-hayduke-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Esker has simplified the Hayduke’s size range with S, M, L, and XL. The new Geo changes include a longer wheelbase, lower center of gravity (increased BB drop), and a taller stack. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-logo-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ve increased the tire clearance to 29 x 3.0″, but say that actual tire clearance will depend on drivetrain choice, rim width, dropout position, and actual tire measurements. Plus, the Hayduke is rockin’ a lil’ more heel clearance, making it easier to ride in hiking boots.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates hayduke tire clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-tire-clearance-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Esker has also added mid-mount rack mounts to the middle of the seat stay. On the titanium frames only, the Hitching Post seat tube bottle boss/gear strap allows for more seat post insertion. The dropper port has been relocated up the seat tube to make it easier to route. Plus, there is a new custom molded chainstay protector.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates hayduke frame Lunar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-Lunar-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Lunar</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates heyduke frame metal flake blue\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-heyduke-frame-metal-flake-blue-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Metal Flake Blue</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates hayduke frame sundry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-frame-sundry-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Sundry</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>New colors for the steel frames include Sundry, Lunar, and Metal Flake Blue. Plus, there are new logos and finishes for the titanium models.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These updates will help the Hayduke be more than ready for backcountry exploration, as well as differentiate the Japhy more. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-geo.webp\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-geo.webp\" alt=\"Eskar Cycles Updates hayduke geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-geo.webp 702w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-geo-297x195.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Eskar-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-geo-120x79.webp 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Hayduke Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Steel Frames: $1000</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steel Completes: Starting at $3000</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Frames: $2500</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Completes: Starting at $4500</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Hayduke LVS Updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"690\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates profile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870-297x160.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870-120x65.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-profile-e1741622358870-768x414.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Hayduke LVS remains almost the same, with some minor changes like increased snack-hauling capabilities with added top tube bolts. Plus, there are some minor geometry updates like increased stack offset and a longer effective top tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"998\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates chainstay yoke\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-297x232.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-120x94.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-768x599.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The mid-seat stay rack mounts carry over from the Hayduke, as well as the Hitching Post seat tube bottle boss/gear strap. There’s also a custom chainstay protector. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates Hitching post hayduke LVS\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Hitching-post-hayduke-LVS-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can expect a new logo and finishes on the titanium versions only. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated LVS Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-LVS-geo.webp\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-LVS-geo.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates hayduke LVS geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-LVS-geo.webp 702w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-LVS-geo-297x195.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-hayduke-LVS-geo-120x79.webp 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>LVS Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frames start: $2950</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Completes: Starting at $4950</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Japhy Updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates Japhy full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Japhy-full-bike-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Following Hayduke’s lead, the new updated Japhy also gets a simplified size range with S, M, L, and XL. Japhy gets updated geo with the increased stack offset and longer effective top tube. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates chainstay yoke\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-chainstay-yoke-1-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ve eliminated the Japhy’s seatstay bridge, making for a more compliant ride. The titanium Japhy gets a new chainstay yoke that has a slimmer profile, as well as the Hitching Post seat tube bottle boss/gear strap update. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates rear dropout\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-dropout-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The dropper port has been relocated higher in the seat tube to ease routing. There is also new bolt-on cable routing allowing for the use of bolt-on frame bags. The removable cable routing also cleans things up with the use of wireless shifting or single-speed configurations.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates metal flake orange\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-metal-flake-orange-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Metal Flake Orange </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates paloverde\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-paloverde-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Paloverde</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates darkness\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-darkness-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Darkness</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Japhy also comes with a new custom chainstay protector. Plus, there is a new logo and finish on the titanium frames and new colors for the steel frames: Paloverde, Darkness, and Metal Flack Orange. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated Japhy Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-japhy-geo.webp\"><img width=\"698\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-japhy-geo.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates japhy geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-japhy-geo.webp 698w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-japhy-geo-297x196.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-japhy-geo-120x79.webp 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Japhy Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Steel Frames: $1000</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steel Completes:  Starting at $3000</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Frames: $2500</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Completes: Starting at $4500</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Lorax Ti Updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates lorax full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-full-bike-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Lorax doesn’t get a boatload of updates but gets slimmer with a sleeker chainstay yoke and improved heel clearance. The seat stays have the mid-mount rack mounts in the middle of the seat stay.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1091\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates rear drop out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out-297x253.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out-120x102.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-rear-drop-out-768x655.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the other bikes, the Lorax gets the Hitching Post to maximize seat post insertion. And the custom chainstay protector shows up again here on the updated Lorax. It also sports a new logo and finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates Lorax Ti welds\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-Lorax-Ti-welds-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-geo.webp\"><img width=\"702\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-geo.webp\" alt=\"Esker Cycles Updates lorax geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-geo.webp 702w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-geo-297x195.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Esker-Cycles-Updates-lorax-geo-120x79.webp 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Lorax Retail</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Ti Frames: $2500</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ti Completes: Starting at $4500</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://eskercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">EskerCycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-cycles-hardtail-lineup-updated-hayduke-lvs-japhy-lorax-ti/\">Esker Cycles Hits the Refresh Button on its Hardtail Lineup</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b4d42e040614b85babc19d129f5deee402ae85ca73df7eca2f134d4f6ee21198","category":"Cycling"}